                    <div class="sec-title">Red Flags</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Single-direction map for isomorphism</strong> — always use bidirectional maps; surjection violations silently pass</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Missing map.put(0,1)</strong> — prefix sum subarray problems break without this initialisation</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>HashMap vs int[26]</strong> — for char-only freq counting use int[26]; 10× faster in Java</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Forgetting equals/hashCode</strong> — custom key objects in Java MUST override both</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>HashMap on sorted data</strong> — sorted array + complement → two-pointer is O(1) space</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>LRU via HashMap alone</strong> — HashMap cannot maintain order; needs DLL or LinkedHashMap</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Negative modulo in Java</strong> — (-1)%k = -1; always add k and re-mod: ((p%k)+k)%k</div>
