                    <div class="sec-title">Red Flags</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>mid = (lo+hi)/2</strong> — classic overflow bug; use mid = lo + (hi-lo)/2 or mid = (lo+hi)&gt;&gt;&gt;1</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>lo &lt; hi vs lo &le; hi</strong> — lo &le; hi is generally safer and easier to reason about</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>BS on answer space without monotone predicate</strong> — if check(mid) doesn't imply check(mid+1), BS is invalid</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Rotated array duplicate handling</strong> — if nums[lo]==nums[mid]==nums[hi], must do lo++, hi-- to shrink</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Forgetting long for mid*mid</strong> — when checking for sqrt, mid*mid can overflow standard integer types</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">🚩 <strong>Incorrectly identifying the sorted half</strong> — in rotated arrays, the check is crucial: if nums[lo] &lt;= nums[mid]...</div>
