            <div class="topic-card" id="tp4">
                <div class="topic-header">
                    <div class="topic-num">04</div>
                    <div style="flex:1">
                        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap">
                            <div class="topic-title">Sliding Window</div>
                            <span class="tier-badge tier-T2">Core DSA</span>
                            <span class="topic-type">Technique</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="topic-meta">45 problems · subarray, substring, frequency maps, deque variants</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-body">
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Converts O(n²) brute-force subarray enumeration into O(n) single-pass solutions by maintaining a live window [left, right] updated incrementally. The "aha" of recognizing when the window should shrink is a genuine test of algorithmic intuition.</div>
                    <div class="core-box"><strong>Core Idea:</strong> The window always represents a valid/optimal range. Instead of recomputing from scratch, add one element at right and remove one at left. The invariant is what makes the window valid — if you can't define it, the technique doesn't apply.</div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Sub-Variants</div>
                    <div class="pill-grid">
                        <span class="pill">Fixed-size window (size K)</span><span class="pill">Variable window: maximize length</span><span class="pill">Variable window: minimize length</span><span class="pill">Window with frequency map</span><span class="pill">Exact-K constraint (atMost trick)</span><span class="pill">At-most-K constraint counting</span><span class="pill">Replacement allowed window</span><span class="pill">Monotonic deque (max/min)</span><span class="pill">2D matrix window</span><span class="pill">Window + binary search</span><span class="pill">Window + prefix sum</span><span class="pill">Circular/wrap-around window</span><span class="pill">String permutation matching</span><span class="pill">Multi-pointer window</span><span class="pill">Counting subarrays (not just find)</span>
                    </div>

