                        Re-solve #1, #3, #6, #17 on a timer: under 12 minutes each from blank editor. For every problem solved, write its one-line invariant AND its decision-tree path (which Q in the Decision Framework does it resolve at?). Do blind classification: take 10 random LeetCode interval problems; before reading constraints carefully, classify them to a sub-variant using only the title and first sentence. Check classification rate. Implement difference array and sweep-line patterns from memory without referencing any code.<br><br>
                        <strong>Phase 3 — Validate (Unseen Sources):</strong><br>
                        AtCoder ABC/ARC problems tagged "intervals" — solve any 5 unseen. Codeforces Div 2 D/E with tags sortings + greedy — solve 3 problems where statements don't mention "interval" but solution requires it. USACO Silver/Gold: "Haybale Stacking", "Lifeguards", "Rental Service" without editorial. Google Kickstart / Hash Code archives — search scheduling or resource-allocation rounds.
