                        <tbody>
                        <tr><td>9</td><td>"You're scheduling tasks across 1000 machines in a distributed system. How does greedy scale?"</td><td>Each machine runs a local greedy scheduler; a global coordinator uses a heap of (next_available_time, machine_id). MapReduce-style partitioning: O(n log k) for k machines.</td></tr>
