                    <div class="sec-title">Two-Heap Complete Implementation Reference</div>
                    <div class="info-box">
                        <strong>Static two-heap (Find Median from Data Stream):</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>import heapq
lower = []   # max-heap (negate): stores the SMALLER half, size = ceil(n/2)
upper = []   # min-heap (default): stores the LARGER half, size = floor(n/2)

def add(val):
    if not lower or val &lt;= -lower[0]:
        heapq.heappush(lower, -val)
    else:
        heapq.heappush(upper, val)
    # rebalance: |lower| - |upper| must be 0 or 1
    if len(lower) &gt; len(upper) + 1:
        heapq.heappush(upper, -heapq.heappop(lower))
    elif len(upper) &gt; len(lower):
        heapq.heappush(lower, -heapq.heappop(upper))

def get_median():
    if len(lower) &gt; len(upper): return float(-lower[0])
    return (-lower[0] + upper[0]) / 2.0</code></pre>
                        <strong>Sliding-window two-heap (Sliding Window Median) with lazy deletion:</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>from collections import defaultdict
lazy = defaultdict(int)   # lazy[v] = times v is marked deleted but not pruned
lower_sz = upper_sz = 0

def _prune(heap, is_lower):
    while heap:
        top = -heap[0] if is_lower else heap[0]
        if lazy[top] &gt; 0:
            lazy[top] -= 1; heapq.heappop(heap)
        else: break

def add_w(val):
    global lower_sz, upper_sz
    if not lower or val &lt;= -lower[0]: heapq.heappush(lower, -val); lower_sz += 1
    else: heapq.heappush(upper, val); upper_sz += 1
    _rebalance_w()

def remove_w(val):
    global lower_sz, upper_sz
    lazy[val] += 1
    if val &lt;= -lower[0]: lower_sz -= 1
    else: upper_sz -= 1
    _rebalance_w()

def _rebalance_w():
    global lower_sz, upper_sz
    while lower_sz &gt; upper_sz + 1:
        _prune(lower, True)
        heapq.heappush(upper, -heapq.heappop(lower))
        lower_sz -= 1; upper_sz += 1
    while upper_sz &gt; lower_sz:
        _prune(upper, False)
        heapq.heappush(lower, -heapq.heappop(upper))
        upper_sz -= 1; lower_sz += 1

def get_median_w():
    _prune(lower, True); _prune(upper, False)
    if lower_sz &gt; upper_sz: return float(-lower[0])
    return (-lower[0] + upper[0]) / 2.0</code></pre>
                    </div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Retroactive Greedy Universal Template</div>
                    <div class="info-box">
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>import heapq
heap   = []   # stores past decisions as (cost_key, metadata)
result = 0    # current state (fuel, health, total cost, etc.)

for item in items:
    heapq.heappush(heap, cost_key(item))   # greedily accept current item
    result = accept(result, item)

    while constraint_violated(result):     # if constraint broken...
        worst = heapq.heappop(heap)        # undo worst past decision
        result = undo(result, worst)

# result = optimal value; len(heap) = optimal count of decisions</code></pre>
                        <strong>Retroactive problems and their heap type:</strong><br>
                        • <strong>LC 871 Refueling Stops</strong> — max-heap of fuel at skipped stations; pop when tank empty = "I retroactively stopped there"<br>
                        • <strong>LC 1642 Furthest Building</strong> — min-heap of climb sizes; pop smallest when size &gt; k = convert that climb to bricks<br>
                        • <strong>CF 1526C Potions</strong> — max-heap of negative potion values; pop worst when health &lt; 0 = never took that potion<br>
                        • <strong>LC 2542 Max Subsequence Score</strong> — min-heap of nums1 values in window; pop when size &gt; k = exclude that element from sum
                    </div>

                    <div class="sec-title">State Evolution Across Stages</div>
                    <div class="info-box">
                        <strong>Stage 1 — Flat array, simple value key:</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>heap = []
for x in arr:
    heapq.heappush(heap, x)        # min-heap; push raw value
    if len(heap) &gt; k:
        heapq.heappop(heap)        # evict the SMALLEST (weakest VIP)
# heap[0] = K-th largest; list(heap) = the K largest (unsorted)</code></pre>
                        <strong>Stage 2 — Derived key (frequency / distance / tuple):</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>from collections import Counter
freq = Counter(arr)
heap = []
for elem, cnt in freq.items():
    heapq.heappush(heap, (cnt, elem))   # tuple: (primary_key, secondary_key)
    if len(heap) &gt; k:
        heapq.heappop(heap)             # evicts the tuple with smallest (cnt, elem)
# Tiebreak: for lexicographic-ascending result, use (-cnt, word)</code></pre>
                        <strong>Stage 3 — Multi-source with source pointer:</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>heap = [(matrix[0][c], 0, c) for c in range(min(k, cols))]
heapq.heapify(heap)
for _ in range(k - 1):
    val, r, c = heapq.heappop(heap)
    if r + 1 &lt; rows:
        heapq.heappush(heap, (matrix[r+1][c], r+1, c))  # advance source
return heapq.heappop(heap)[0]</code></pre>
                        <strong>Stage 5 — QuickSelect O(n) replaces O(n log K):</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>import random
def quickselect(nums, lo, hi, k_idx):
    if lo &gt;= hi: return nums[lo]
    pivot_pos = random.randint(lo, hi)
    nums[pivot_pos], nums[hi] = nums[hi], nums[pivot_pos]
    i = lo
    for j in range(lo, hi):
        if nums[j] &gt;= nums[hi]:
            nums[i], nums[j] = nums[j], nums[i]
            i += 1
    nums[i], nums[hi] = nums[hi], nums[i]
    if i == k_idx:  return nums[i]
    elif i &gt; k_idx: return quickselect(nums, lo, i - 1, k_idx)
    else:            return quickselect(nums, i + 1, hi, k_idx)
# K-th largest = quickselect(nums, 0, n-1, k-1)</code></pre>
                        <strong>Stage 5 — Bucket sort O(n) for bounded frequency:</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0"><code>from collections import Counter
freq   = Counter(nums)
bucket = [[] for _ in range(len(nums) + 1)]
for elem, cnt in freq.items():
    bucket[cnt].append(elem)
result = []
for f in range(len(bucket) - 1, 0, -1):
    result.extend(bucket[f])
    if len(result) &gt;= k:
        return result[:k]</code></pre>
