                    <div class="sec-title">Mastery Problem Set (30 problems · 5 stages)</div>
                    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
                        <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Layer</th><th>Stage</th><th>Source</th><th>Problem</th><th>Diff</th><th>P</th><th>Sub-Variant / New Idea</th><th>Key Insight</th></tr></thead>
                        <tbody>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">1</td><td><span class="l1">Foundation</span></td><td>1</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/unique-paths/" target="_blank">LC 62</a> Unique Paths</td><td><span class="diff-m">Med</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Path counting, no obstacles</td><td class="insight">THE baseline — dp[i][j] = dp[i-1][j] + dp[i][j-1]; entire first row and first column = 1; answer = dp[m-1][n-1]; establishes the 2D grid flood mental model</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">2</td><td><span class="l1">Foundation</span></td><td>1</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-path-sum/" target="_blank">LC 64</a> Minimum Path Sum</td><td><span class="diff-m">Med</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Min-cost path (corner to corner)</td><td class="insight">dp[i][j] = grid[i][j] + min(dp[i-1][j], dp[i][j-1]); same structure as #1, only the operation changes (min+accumulate vs. count); operation-swap pattern</td></tr>
