                        <tr><td class="num-cell">4</td><td><span class="l1">Foundation</span></td><td>2</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/triangle/" target="_blank">LC 120</a> Triangle</td><td><span class="diff-m">Med</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Min path on jagged grid</td><td class="insight">Bottom-up in-place: triangle[i][j] += min(triangle[i+1][j], triangle[i+1][j+1]); answer = triangle[0][0]; jagged shape requires j ∈ [0, i]</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">5</td><td><span class="l1">Foundation</span></td><td>2</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-falling-path-sum/" target="_blank">LC 931</a> Minimum Falling Path Sum</td><td><span class="diff-m">Med</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Min path, free start column</td><td class="insight">Entire first row = grid values (all valid starts); answer = min(dp[n-1]) over all columns; answer aggregation changes from single cell to row minimum</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">6</td><td><span class="l1">Foundation</span></td><td>2</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/dungeon-game/" target="_blank">LC 174</a> Dungeon Game</td><td><span class="diff-h">Hard</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Min HP path, reverse DP</td><td class="insight">Hard: forward DP fails because min-cost path ≠ max-survival path; state = min HP needed to survive → forces reverse traversal; max(1, ...) enforces HP ≥ 1</td></tr>
