                        <tr><td class="num-cell">8</td><td><span class="l2">Variants</span></td><td>2</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/minimum-falling-path-sum-ii/" target="_blank">LC 1289</a> Minimum Falling Path Sum II</td><td><span class="diff-h">Hard</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Non-same-column constraint</td><td class="insight">Hard: naïve O(n³); O(n²) requires min1/min2 trick — if prev min was at same column, use min2; otherwise use min1; track min1_col</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">9</td><td><span class="l2">Variants</span></td><td>2</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-non-negative-product-in-a-matrix/" target="_blank">LC 1594</a> Maximum Non-Negative Product in a Matrix</td><td><span class="diff-m">Med</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">Dual min/max tracking on grid path</td><td class="insight">Track both max_dp[i][j] and min_dp[i][j]; negative × negative = positive; same right/down movement but need both extremes per cell</td></tr>
                        <tr><td class="num-cell">10</td><td><span class="l2">Variants</span></td><td>2</td><td>LeetCode</td><td class="prob-name"><a class="lc-link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/out-of-boundary-paths/" target="_blank">LC 576</a> Out of Boundary Paths</td><td><span class="diff-m">Med</span></td><td></td><td class="variant-cell">3D DP (position + step counter)</td><td class="insight">dp[i][j][k] = ways to leave grid from (i,j) in k steps; all 4 directions valid; out-of-bounds step contributes 1; modular arithmetic throughout</td></tr>
