                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Stage 4 Follow-Ups:</strong></div>
                    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
                        <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Question</th><th>Intended Answer Direction</th></tr></thead>
                        <tbody>
                        <tr><td>5</td><td>"How would you find the Shortest Common Supersequence of THREE strings?"</td><td>Generalise SCS: dp[i][j][k] for three string prefixes; O(n³); the 2-string formula SCS = n+m-LCS does not extend cleanly to 3+ strings; must use true 3D DP</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>6</td><td>"In interleaving strings, what if the interleaving must preserve relative order within each WORD (not character)?"</td><td>New state: dp[wi][wj] where wi = words consumed from s1, wj from s2; match check is word-level equality; same boolean DP structure, unit of comparison changes from character to word</td></tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table></div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Stage 5 Follow-Ups:</strong></div>
                    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
