                        <tr><td>7</td><td>"LCS of two strings each of length 10⁵. How do you avoid the O(nm) DP?"</td><td>LCS → LIS reduction: for each char of s1, find its positions in s2 in reverse order; concatenate position lists; run O(n log n) LIS (tails + binary search)</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>8</td><td>"Longest Repeating Substring for n=10⁵ — what's the optimal approach?"</td><td>Suffix array + LCP array: build SA in O(n log n), compute LCP in O(n); answer = max(LCP array); total O(n log n) — vs O(n²) DP</td></tr>
