                    <div class="sec-title">Graduation Test</div>
                    <div class="info-box">
                        These three problems are NOT in the table above. Solving all three cold (no hints, no editorial, 45 min each) certifies full mastery.<br><br>
                        <strong>Test 1 — LC 1458: Max Dot Product of Two Subsequences</strong> (Stage 3 + Stage 4)<br>
                        <em>Primary stage: Stage 3.</em> Combination: Stage 4 (recognise as LCS-style DP where the "match value" is A[i]*B[j] — a product, not equality check) + Stage 3 (state must handle negative products: the "start fresh at current pair" branch A[i-1]*B[j-1] alone is needed; base case must be -∞ not 0). Why it certifies mastery: The reduction from "max dot product of subsequences" to "weighted LCS" is a Stage 4 recognition. The need for a "start fresh" branch and -∞ base case is a Stage 3 state-expansion insight. Solving cold proves both layers activate simultaneously.<br><br>
                        <strong>Test 2 — CF 1063F: String Journey</strong> (Stage 4 + Stage 5)<br>
                        <em>Primary stage: Stage 5.</em> Combination: Stage 4 (recognise that checking if a suffix is a subsequence of the adjacent suffix reduces to a string comparison problem on substrings of length k) + Stage 5 (the O(n²) DP TLEs; Z-function or suffix array with LCP gives O(n) per step → O(n) total). Why it certifies mastery: The hidden structure (suffix vs. suffix subsequence relationship = substring comparison) is non-obvious Stage 4 work. The O(n) suffix-based optimisation is Stage 5. Both must fire on an unseen Codeforces Div 1 problem.<br><br>
                        <strong>Test 3 — LC 2707: Extra Characters in a String + Extended to weighted dictionary</strong> (Stage 3 + Stage 4 + Stage 5)<br>
                        <em>Primary stage: Stage 4.</em> Combination: Stage 3 (standard word-break DP with extra character count) + Stage 4 (when dictionary is given as a list of (word, weight) pairs and you must maximise total weight of matched words) + Stage 5 (naïve O(n²·L) inner loop; trie reduces to O(n·L) per position). Why it certifies mastery: The extension from "minimise extra chars" to "maximise weighted match" changes the recurrence operation (min → max) and base case semantics — a Stage 3 state insight. The trie integration for O(L) lookup per position is Stage 5. All three layers must combine cleanly on an unseen variant. A cold solve within 45 minutes certifies full String DP mastery.
                    </div>
