                    <div class="sec-title">State Evolution for Each Sub-Variant Group</div>
                    <div class="info-box" style="line-height:1.75">
                        <strong>Group 1: BIT/Seg-Tree DP (LIS)</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0;font-size:.78rem"><code>Na&iuml;ve: dp[i] = 1 + max over j&lt;i where a[j]&lt;a[i] of dp[j]. O(n&sup2;).

BIT optimisation (O(n log n)):
  Coord-compress a[] to [1, n].
  BIT[v] = max dp[j] over processed j with a[j] = v.
  For each i:
    dp[i] = 1 + BIT.query_prefix_max(a[i] - 1)   # QUERY first
    BIT.update(a[i], dp[i])                       # UPDATE after

Stage 3 (counting LIS): BIT stores (max_len, count) tuple.
  Merge rule: if lengths equal, SUM counts.
  (best_len, best_cnt) = BIT.query(a[i]-1)
  dp_len[i] = best_len + 1
  dp_cnt[i] = best_cnt if best_len &gt; 0 else 1</code></pre>
                        <strong>Group 2: Monotonic Deque DP (max length &isin; [1, K])</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0;font-size:.78rem"><code>Deque of indices j, increasing index order, DECREASING dp values.
At step i:
  1. Pop FRONT while deque.front() &lt; i - K          (expired)
  2. dp[i] = a[i] + dp[deque.front()]               (use max)
  3. Pop BACK while dp[deque.back()] &le; dp[i-1]     (dominated)
  4. Push i-1 to back
O(n); each element pushed/popped at most once.</code></pre>
                        <strong>Group 3: CHT</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0;font-size:.78rem"><code>Canonical: dp[i] = min over j of: dp[j] + m[j]*x[i] + c[j]
Line L_j: y = m[j]*t + b[j]  where b[j] = dp[j] + c[j]

Stage 1 (monotone slopes AND queries): Deque CHT. O(n).
Stage 2 (mono slopes, non-mono queries): Binary search on deque. O(n log n).
Stage 3 (non-mono slopes): Li Chao tree. O(n log V).</code></pre>
                        <strong>Group 4: D&amp;C DP (per layer t)</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0;font-size:.78rem"><code>solve(l, r, opt_lo, opt_hi):
  mid = (l + r) // 2
  scan j in [opt_lo, min(opt_hi, mid-1)] to find opt(mid)
  dp[t][mid] = best
  solve(l, mid-1, opt_lo, opt_mid)
  solve(mid+1, r, opt_mid, opt_hi)
O(n log n) per layer; O(kn log n) total.</code></pre>
                        <strong>Group 5: Knuth&apos;s (interval DP)</strong>
                        <pre style="white-space:pre-wrap;margin:.4rem 0;font-size:.78rem"><code>Fill by INCREASING interval length d = j - i.
  for d in 1..n-1:
    for i in 0..n-1-d:
      j = i + d
      for k in opt[i][j-1]..opt[i+1][j]:
        update dp[i][j], opt[i][j]
O(n&sup2;) total by telescoping on opt bounds.
Pre-check: verify QI before applying.</code></pre>
                    </div>
